annotationA: Small nuclear ribonucleoprotein G is a Sm class protein and a common component of pre-mRNA processing U snRNPs. It forms the toroidal core of U snRNPs (Sm core domain) together with 6 related Sm proteins
annotationB: U4-U6 small nuclear riboprotein factor 60K; U6 snRNA binding; U4 snRNA binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: RNA splicing; mRNA splicing, via spliceosome
